:: No more {"position":"1700,300","size":"100,100"}
Centre Point is still behind you. It's been there all night long.

The way that you conceive, now, of its height is more temporal than spatial and like time but not but like space it remains impossible, merely notional; has a quality that space only attains when we imagine it infinitely.

One jumping from the top should fall forever and seem to fall as a ton of feathers falls in a perfect vacuum.

Standing here you can see London, Carthage, Liverpool and everything else.

(if: $hadPhoneCall is true)[You think of Aoife. The baby. The cold flat waiting for you with nothing in it but your failure.]

