:: The Stranger at the French {"position":"300,700","size":"100,100"}
As you approach them someone else catches your eye.

He is a skeleton, clad in leathers that serve for his skin. His suedehead veils the clean dome of a skull which, were its architecture less Roman, might seem vulnerable, but is, in its neoclassical form, more embolos than eggshell.

You know him as an old friend, from whom you are estranged over some personal business. He eyes you, raising his empty glass, then tilts his head, like a curious velociraptor, towards the bar. He is offering you a drink.

[[Accept his offer|His round]]


:: The coast of Carthage {"position":"100,1550","size":"100,100"}
You bottled it but you've found safe harbour in Carthage, which is not like you remember it at all. These days it is swamped with Romans.

The last time you were here, you recall only Scipio Aemilianus, who was weeping and who said:

<div class="verse">
'A day will come when Ilium shall perish,
And Priam and his people shall be slain.'
</div>

You think about that still, sometimes, in England.

You see two paths:

On the hill a woman burns upon a pyre.

And past the beach, a little bar: The Green Sea.

[[Approach the pyre|Dido]]
(if: $haunts's length >= 3)[[[Go to The Green Sea|LINE 2]]](else:)[//The Green Sea feels distant.//]
[[Wake from this dream|Dean Street]]


:: The critic's judgement {"position":"300,1400","size":"100,100"}
(set: $confidence to $confidence - 5)

He nods, pulls the manuscript towards him. He lights another cigarette.

The bar, which had been very loud, seems quieter now, while he reads the title page then turns immediately to somewhere in the middle.

He reads a little there, then turns again to another page and reads that too. He does this several times, while the bar is getting louder in your ears, until it seems about to drop.

'Not for me', he says. 'Have you tried America?'

You thank him, say goodbye, and make to leave but he calls you back:

'And by the way, tell Copper I said hello.'

(set: $knowsCopperWord to true)

He pauses, as if remembering something.

'Oh — and if you're ever in Cecil Court, look up the antiquarian. Queer fellow, but he knows things. Things about books that shouldn't exist.'

(set: $knowsCecilCourt to true)

[[Try again|Dean Street]]
[[Head for the night bus|Meet Jeffrey Bernard]]


